    <title>one is one is 0.999999...</title>
    <url>/til/2020/04/28/one-is-one-is-0-999999/</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<p>The number 1 and 0.999999…(9s forever) is actually the exact same number.</p>
<p>There’s several simple proofs of this you can consider.</p>
<figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">1&#x2F;3 &#x3D; 0.333...</span><br><span class="line">3 x 1&#x2F;3 &#x3D; 0.999...</span><br><span class="line">but also 1</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>

<figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">x - y &#x3D; 0</span><br><span class="line">x &#x3D; y</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">1 - 0.999...(forever) &#x3D; 0.000... (forever)</span><br><span class="line">1 &#x3D; 0.999...</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>

]]></content>
